Package: ASPEN
Title: Allele-specific expression and imbalance modelling of F1 hybrids in single-cell data
Version: 1.1.2
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Veronika", "Petrova", , "v.petrova@victorchang.edu.au", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID")),
      person("Emily", "Wong", , "e.wong@victorchang.edu.au", role = c("aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID")))
Description: ASPEN represents a comprehensive statistical framework that is designed to evaluate patterns 
            in allele-specific expression (ASE). ASPEN uses beta-binomial distribution to model allelic ratio, 
            a fraction of reads from a reference allele to the total number of reads mapped to a gene. 
